# Phase 2: Client Operations Portal

**Priority:** HIGH — Required before commercial launch
**Dependency:** Phase 1 (partial — manufacturers and products must exist in the catalog)
**Stack:** Next.js 14 App Router · Prisma · Supabase Auth · TypeScript
**Dev Server:** `npm run dev` — runs at **http://localhost:5000**
**Deployment:** Vercel (serverless)

> **Context:** WhyFire's biggest weakness is zero dealer self-service. This portal is our differentiator — full catalog control, real-time change visibility, and account management pulled from our Airtable client DB.

---

## Plan 2-A: Dealer Account Auth & Onboarding ✅ LARGELY COMPLETE
*Target: Dealer sign-in, account creation, and protected portal access*

### What's Done
- `DealerAccount` Prisma model linked to Supabase `userId` with slug-based portal routing
- `src/middleware.ts` handles Supabase session checks and route protection
- Login page at `/dealer/[slug]/login` with email/password via Supabase Auth
- Dealer portal layout at `/dealer/[slug]/layout.tsx` — session-aware with sidebar nav
- Admin user management at `/admin/dealer-portal/users` with invite modal and edit modal
- API routes: `/api/admin/users` (list/create), `/api/admin/users/[id]` (update/delete)
- `/api/dealer/[slug]/settings/users` for dealer-scoped user management
- Auth utility functions in `src/lib/auth-utils.ts`
- `DealerHeaderUser.tsx` component for dealer portal header with user info
- Role-based access (admin vs dealer) via Supabase user metadata

### Remaining Work
- [ ] Forgot Password page (`/forgot-password`) — Supabase magic link / reset flow
- [ ] First-time welcome/setup page for newly provisioned dealers
- [ ] Email notification on invite (SendGrid/SES integration)
- [ ]
